+## Sprint 8 Commission Divers — Core Build
+
+- Confirmed schema, commission-catalog module (Sprint 1), and QuickAddPartyDialog (Sprint 2) already matched M10 spec exactly — no gaps found before building.
+- Added `commission` module: `commission.types.ts`, `commission.service.ts` (create/list/soft-delete), controller, routes at `/api/commissions`.
+- Added generic `CommissionDynamicFields` client component interpreting the catalog's fieldSchema convention (`string`/`string?`/`period`/`enum:a,b`) — built once, works for all seeded types and any future super_admin-created type.
+- Added `CreateCommissionDialog`, `CommissionsPage` (list + type filter + soft-delete), nav/route wiring.
+
+## Sprint 8 Commission Divers — Runtime Smoke
+
+- Runtime-tested all 6 active types (Mobile Money, Transfert et Change, Visa, Location de Voiture, Hébergement, Assurance Voyage) plus Canal+ after live activation.
+- Confirmed Client/référent quick-add flow works from inside the commission entry dialog.
+- Confirmed soft-delete (admin+) removes a commission from the default list.
+- Confirmed a super_admin-created custom type ("Course du mois") appears correctly in the entry dialog with zero code change.
+
+## Sprint 8 Commission Divers — Note Column + Type Editor
+
+- Added `note` (optional text) as a common column on `commission_transactions` — universal across all types, not per-type fieldSchema. Closed real gap: Transfert et Change, Visa, Canal+ had no way to record transaction context.
+- Added `commissionCatalogApi.update()` client method (server-side `updateCommissionType` already supported `fieldSchema` edits since Sprint 1, nothing client-side ever called it).
+- Added `EditCommissionTypeDialog` (Settings, super_admin) — add/remove/rename fields, pick kind (text/optional text/period/enum-with-options), serializes back to the fieldSchema string convention.
+
+## Sprint 8 Commission Divers — Correction Approval Workflow
+
+- New table `commission_edit_requests` (+ `commission_edit_status` enum: pending/approved/rejected). Not in the original M10 spec — added per real business need (agent mistake correction without allowing silent direct edits, especially on `commissionAmount`).
+- Considered three designs explicitly before building: (A) direct edit fully audited, (B) lock amount only, (C) full approval queue. Chose C per explicit decision.
+- Service: `createEditRequest` (agent+, mandatory reason, blocks a second pending request on the same transaction), `approveEditRequest` (admin+, applies exact proposed patch atomically), `rejectEditRequest` (admin+, transaction untouched).
+- List endpoint enriches each commission with `pendingEditRequestId` via one bulk query, not N+1.
+- Frontend: `RequestCommissionEditDialog` (scoped to date/amount/note only — client/référent and type-specific fields deliberately out of this first pass), `CommissionEditQueuePage` (admin+, before/after diff table, requester name via users lookup, approve/reject with optional rejection note), pending badge on the commission list.
+
+## Sprint 8 Commission Divers — Bugs Found
+
+- Client `CommissionType` type never exposed `fieldSchema` despite the server already returning it — would have made the dynamic-field renderer silently render nothing. Caught before shipping the entry dialog.
+- Used `<DialogTrigger asChild>` out of habit (Radix convention) — this project uses Base UI, which doesn't support that prop. Confirmed via grep that every other dialog in the codebase uses the plain `<DialogTrigger><Button/></DialogTrigger>` pattern; fixed to match.
+
+## Sprint 8 Commission Divers — Validation
+
+- `npm run typecheck -w packages/server`: PASS (run after every stage: core build, note+editor, correction workflow).
+- `cd packages/client && npx tsc --noEmit`: PASS (same cadence).
+- `npm test` (vitest, Sprint 5's penalty accrual suite): PASS throughout, unaffected.
+
+## Sprint 8 Commission Divers — Closed
+
+- Sprint marked closed in TASKS.md (2026-07-16). All 5 original checklist items confirmed via runtime test, plus three beyond-scope additions (note column, type editor, correction workflow) fully built and tested.
+- Deferred, not forgotten: hard-delete for unused types (soft-disable confirmed sufficient for now), commission Settings tab filter capability, and correction-request coverage for client/référent/type-specific fields.
